h2. Feature Request

Add support for multiple arguments to logging methods.

h2. Test case

{code:lang=javascript|title=app.js}
Ti.API.log({sdf:"df"}, [1,3,5,6], "sdfsdf");
{code}

h2. Logs

With the above code, you would see the following result:

{code:lang=none}
Object [1,3,5,6] "sdfsdf"
{code}

Also see attached image

comments.body:
On second thoughts, I agree with the reasons that I presume Matt marked this as invalid, although he should have provided his reasons.

Arguments can be concatenated in Javascript. For example:

{code:lang=javascript}
Ti.API.log({sdf:"df"} + ' ' + [1,3,5,6] + ' ' +  "sdfsdf");
{code}

Why isn't this sufficient?

Sindre

I realise that you are capable of writing this, but a colleague of mine kindly wrote it for you. It's not been tested, but I am sure it's almost there.

Cheers

{code:lang=javascript|title=logger.js}
exports.log = function() {
    var log = '';
    for(var i = 0, len = arguments.length; i < len; i++){
        switch(typeof(arguments[i])) {
            case 'object':
            case 'array':
                log += ' '+JSON.stringify(arguments[i]);
            break;
            case 'string':
            case 'number':
                log += ' '+arguments[i];
            break;
            case 'boolean':
                log += ' '+ (arguments[i]) ? 'true' : 'false';
            break;
            case 'undefined':
                log += ' undefined';
            break;
            default:
                log += ' null';
        }
    }
    Ti.API.info(log);
};
{code}

{code:lang=javascript|title=app.js (Usage)}
var console = require('/logger');
console.log({sdf:"df"}, [1,3,5,6], "sdfsdf");
{code}
